President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the State of South Dakota, providing federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts following severe storms and flooding that occurred between July 21 and July 30, 2010. The declaration allows for federal funding to be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures in several counties. Mark A. Neveau has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.